<TITLE> Women may see collateral-free biz loans </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 29 (bdnews24.com) - The government is mulling collateral-free loans for women entrepreneurs, the finance minister said Sunday. "I'm not promising you; but we'll take all the necessary steps so that the banks give you credits without any collateral," AMA Muhith told women entrepreneurs at the opening ceremony of the 'Women's National Business Agenda' at the Diploma Engineers Institute in the capital. The government was also considering to strengthening the Karmasansthan (Employment) Bank to facilitate such loans, he said. The minister said in Bangladesh, Grameenbank gives credit without security in some sectors. "But the amount is trifling," said the minister. Citing the example of India where collateral-free credit is common for small and medium enterprises, he said: "We now have to think about all government and private banks giving such credit." Home minister Sahara Khatun and Bangladesh Bank governor Salehuddin Ahmed, among others, attended the inaugural session of the programme, organised by Bangladesh Women Chamber of Commerce and Industries. bdne
